15/12/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President-elect Traian Basescu opened consultations Tuesday (14 December) on forming the next cabinet. 
Calin Popescu Tariceanu of Basescu's centre-right Justice and Truth Alliance will be given the first opportunity to assemble a ruling coalition. 
He has already started negotiating with the Humanist Party, which ran with Prime Minister Adrian Nastase's Social Democrats in the recent elections, and with the Democratic Union of Hungarians in Romania.
In other news, US and European Commission (EC) officials have offered their congratulations to Basescu. 
EC President Jose Manuel Durao Barroso said his election comes at an historic moment -- the finalisation of EU accession talks. 
(Rompres - 15/12/04; Reuters, UPI - 14/12/04)
